The paper deals with a remote estimation problem involving communication and energy harvesting, which suggests that it could belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) or Systems and Control (cs.SY) categories. The use of dynamic programming and optimization techniques suggests that it could also belong to the Mathematical Optimization (cs.MA) category. Additionally, the paper deals with a decentralized decision-making problem, which suggests that it could belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) category. Finally, the paper deals with a statistical estimation problem, which suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) category.
